#USMCA is a huge win for our producers.

Its implementation will stimulate the economy, create new jobs, and increase exports with two of North Dakota’s top trading partners.

It’s a shame this agreement was held up for over a year, but I’m thankful we got this done. https://twitter.com/politico/status/1217852324619735041 …

Phase One includes China committing to purchase $200 billion of American products over two years, with at least $40 billion for agricultural goods, while also pledging to stop intellectual property theft and currency manipulation.

This deal is a major victory for the United States and for North Dakota!

I thank President @realDonaldTrump for fighting tirelessly to deliver trade deals that are good for North Dakota’s producers and put American interests first. https://twitter.com/WhiteHouse/status/1217514252023619584 …

Good to meet the new NDDOT Director, Bill Panos!

I appreciate the update on North Dakota’s transportation needs, including passing the Highway Bill and prioritizing investment in rural infrastructure. pic.twitter.com/2d9v10CDjp

Whether through personal animosity toward @POTUS or a misunderstanding of the importance of deterring our enemies, some in the Senate are advocating for changes to make our country less safe.

I will not support their effort and I urge the rest of my colleagues to do the same.

Whether through an existing AUMF or the War Powers Act, President @realDonaldTrump was well within the legal bounds to take action against a known terrorist sitting in Iraq plotting attacks against the United States.

It would have been culpable negligence to not act.

I want to emphasize an overlooked point: Soleimani was killed in Iraq, not Iran.

He was with another known terrorist driving to meet militia members who fired rockets at Americans – killing an American contractor – and tried to storm our embassy, which is sovereign US territory.

Delivered remarks on the Senate floor today opposing the War Powers Act resolution being debated by Congress.

More than anything else, the military and intellectual assets in North Dakota are what motivated me to see the value and importance of a Space Force. 

Thanks to the tireless leadership and help from President @realDonaldTrump, @VP, & our allies in Congress, it became a reality. https://twitter.com/gfherald/status/1215773470455468033 …
With heightened tensions across the world, and an increased focus on space as the next warfighting domain, installations like Cavalier are as important as ever.

We participated in a ribbon cutting ceremony for Cavalier’s SCIF, which allows crewmembers to access timely intelligence on missile threat systems and adversary capabilities.

Thank you to our gracious hosts and to all who serve our nation here! pic.twitter.com/BcQEyy9U9G
Thank you to General Raymond and our military leaders for making this possible!

News: @SpaceForceCSO announced a $700 per-month incentive pay for each person stationed in Cavalier Air Force Station, effective as soon as possible. 
 
This incentive pay will help with recruitment and improve the lives of the crewmembers serving here.

Before our student town hall, @SpaceForceCSO & I met with @UNDAerospace faculty to tour their facilities & hear how they train the next generation of space explorers.

Now we're off to the Cavalier Air Force Station for a tour, ribbon cutting ceremony, and a special announcement. pic.twitter.com/sU0bbkW2Vx

Here at the @UofNorthDakota Aerospace school with @SpaceForceCSO General Raymond of the newly formed @SpaceForceDoD.

We’re starting the day meeting with faculty and staff, touring the facility, and talking with students about the opportunities Space Force presents. pic.twitter.com/7n4ed9nxe7

I thank @SecBernhardt for his work — including on the issuance of new and improved maps —and I encourage landowners to engage in this process.

Find more information here:  https://bit.ly/2QETI9o

I am confident this process will produce mutually beneficial results, building on important FWS guidance which instructs the agency to be cooperative, willing partners while limiting the use of law enforcement officers.
Providing quality maps is fundamental to defining property ownership, and establishing an appeals process ensures we follow due process and protect people's private property rights.

News: Following @SecBernhardt's visit to Hope, North Dakota in October, @USFWS is issuing a Director’s Order to provide due process for landowners who have perpetual FWS easements pre-dating 1976 on their property. pic.twitter.com/SAaYlMN6UU
